## Technical Patterns

### 1. Iterative Concept Validation

#### Description
A pattern that involves rapid prototyping and testing of product concepts to validate assumptions and gather feedback early in the development cycle. This iterative approach ensures that concepts are aligned with user needs and market demands.

#### Implementation Notes
- Key considerations include setting clear validation metrics, using MVPs (Minimum Viable Products) for testing, and incorporating user feedback loops to refine concepts.

