### 2. Version Control for Concept Management

#### Description
Utilizing version control systems (e.g., Git) to manage and track the evolution of product concepts. This pattern ensures that concept iterations are documented, changes are traceable, and collaboration among team members is streamlined.

#### Implementation Notes
- Best practices include regular commits, branching for experimentation, and using status indicators to monitor concept development progress.

